==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emaciation
<hw>E*ma`ci*a"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧maciation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of making
very lean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being emaciated or reduced to excessive
leanness; an excessively lean condition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emaculate</ent>⟦br⟧
